    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "The Prophet Muhammad (SAWW), as transmitted through the chain of Imams back to Imam al-Baqir (AS), declared that Paradise is reserved first for him among the prophets, and among all peoples, his Ahlul Bayt's followers (Shi'ah) will enter Paradise first. This hadith from al-Amali al-Mufid establishes the special eschatological status of both the Prophet and the Shi'ah of Ahlul Bayt, emphasizing the centrality of loyalty to the Prophet's household in the afterlife.",
        "key_terms": {
          "الجنة": "Paradise (Jannah) -- the abode of the righteous in the afterlife",
          "شيعتنا": "Our Shi'ah -- literally 'our partisans/followers', referring to the devoted followers of Ahlul Bayt",
          "أهل البيت": "Ahlul Bayt -- the People of the House, the Prophet's household including Ali, Fatima, Hasan, and Husain"
        },
        "seo_question": "What did the Prophet Muhammad say about Paradise and the Shi'ah of Ahlul Bayt?"
      },
